   - "For ITEM-0002, a local or in-memory adapter is acceptable only if its interface and records remain Aurora-shaped, tenant-scoped, and replaceable by real persistence later"
   - "For ITEM-0002, any assistant implementation should sit behind a thin adapter boundary so Bedrock can replace the stub without rewriting route contracts"
   - "For ITEM-0002, uploads, file references, OAuth completion, migrations, and infra/resource wiring remain explicitly deferred"
+  - "ITEM-0002 implementation derives server tenant scope from runtimeConfig.tenantId, with public tenant config used only for display"
+  - "ITEM-0002 streaming contract is SSE-style frames returned from POST /api/chat over a ReadableStream and consumed by fetch() on the client"
+  - "ITEM-0002 persistence contract uses Aurora-shaped session and message records with tenant_id, user_id, session_id, timestamps, and citation metadata even when backed by a local adapter"
+  - "ITEM-0003 stays inside apps/web plus allowed baton files; do not reopen infra delivery, root workspace/bootstrap work, or broader auth completion in this slice"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, implement POST /api/files as a tenant-scoped multipart upload route that validates file count, per-file size, session-level file-count limits, and MIME type on the server before persisting any uploaded files"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, limit supported upload types in this slice to the success-criteria document formats: PDF, DOCX, and TXT"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, reject invalid upload requests without partial success semantics; if any file violates the slice constraints, the request should fail as a whole"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, a local/dev object storage adapter is acceptable only if it preserves S3-shaped metadata and ownership fields so real S3 wiring can replace it later without changing route contracts"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, persist Aurora-shaped session_file records including tenant_id, user_id, session_id, file_id, original_name, sanitized_name, content_type, size_bytes, storage key, status, and timestamps"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, uploaded file ownership must be validated by tenantId, userId, and sessionId before fileIds can be attached to chat turns"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, extend the existing chat contract only enough to accept fileIds, associate them with the saved user message when applicable, and expose bounded attachment context to the assistant stub for subsequent turns"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, GET /api/sessions/:id/messages may include session-scoped file metadata and saved message attachment metadata so the UI can reload available attachments without adding a separate file-list route in this slice"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, defer presigned download URLs, lifecycle cleanup jobs, virus scanning, and real Bedrock/S3/AWS resource wiring"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, perform all request validation before persisting any file or metadata; invalid uploads fail atomically for the whole request rather than returning partial success"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, use multipart/form-data for POST /api/files and derive tenant scope only from server runtime configuration, never from request fields, query params, or client headers"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, the dev storage seam may keep file bytes locally or in process memory, but it must return an S3-shaped key following the intended ownership hierarchy so the contract can be swapped for real object storage later"
+  - "For ITEM-0003, chat attachment context should stay bounded to a small recent set of ready files within the current session and should be passed to the assistant seam as metadata/source references, not as broad raw-byte hydration logic"
+  - "ITEM-0004 primarily targets infra/cdk and replaces placeholder stack outputs with real PoC infrastructure definitions for SharedStack, TenantStack, and UIStack"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, keep the deployment model locked to one shared Nuxt image in ECR with one ECS/Fargate service per tenant receiving deploy-time env/config for tenant identity"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, SharedStack must provision the core shared platform baseline: VPC, ECS cluster, ALB, Aurora Serverless v2, Secrets Manager-backed database/admin secret handling, shared attachments bucket, ECR repository, and coherent shared log/parameter resources"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, TenantStack must preserve hard tenant isolation by provisioning one tenant docs bucket, one Bedrock Knowledge Base, one Bedrock Agent plus alias, one tenant schema setup path, one ingestion scheduler, and tenant-scoped IAM/log resources per tenant"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, UIStack must provision the per-tenant Nuxt SSR ECS service and ALB listener-rule wiring needed for the same-image-per-tenant contract, including deploy-time tenant env vars and secret-backed runtime config"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, it is acceptable to use pragmatic PoC-level CDK constructs or custom-resource shims where AWS service coverage is awkward, but the named resource categories cannot remain placeholders or manual console steps"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, keep application architecture unchanged: no separate API service, no Lambda application backend, and no client-controlled tenant routing shortcut"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, root workspace/bootstrap normalization, CI/CD automation, production hardening, and broad operational tooling remain deferred unless a minimal in-scope file under apps/web or infra/cdk is required to make the CDK deployment contract coherent"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, add a concrete in-repo tenant/environment configuration source so the CDK app can instantiate SharedStack once and TenantStack/UIStack per tenant without ad hoc context flags for the primary deploy path"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, replace the existing placeholder-only stack outputs rather than layering new intent-only outputs beside them"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, SharedStack owns shared platform primitives only; tenant Bedrock resources, tenant docs buckets, tenant schema/bootstrap resources, and tenant ECS services belong in the per-tenant stacks"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, UIStack may depend on SharedStack and its corresponding TenantStack outputs, but must preserve one ECS service per tenant using the same application image with deploy-time tenant identity"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, acceptable PoC shims include custom resources for Aurora schema/bootstrap work and awkward Bedrock coverage, but `cdk deploy --all` still needs a coherent end-to-end resource graph"
+  - "For ITEM-0004, removing the hidden image-push prerequisite is more important than preserving a manual-tag flow: UIStack may build the shared Nuxt image from `apps/web` as a CDK container asset for PoC deployability, while SharedStack still provisions the explicit ECR repository for later promotion/CI wiring"
